{
  "key": "HADOOP-58",
  "project": "HADOOP",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Hadoop requires configuration of hadoop-site.xml or won't run",
    "description": "On a new install, I would expect '${HADOOP_HOME}/bin/start-all.sh\" to bring up a basic instance, one that is using local filesystem (Or if not, then uses a DFS homed in localhost:/tmp) and that has all four daemons running on localhost.  Currently this is not the case.  Hadoop complains 'java.lang.RuntimeException: Not a host:port pair: local'.  It doesn't like the 'local' default value for mapred.job.tracker and fs.default.name properties.\n\nRevision: 379930\n\n",
    "created": "2006-02-24 03:43:08+00:00",
